<h4>Qualifications For Voting</h4>
The criteria for being qualified to vote differs from state to state.
In order to register to vote in New Jersey, you must meet the following criteria:
<ol>
  <li>Be a United States Citizen</li>
  <li>Be at least 17 years old, though you are not permitted to vote till you have reached the age of 18</li>
  <li>Be a resident of the country for 30 days before the election</li>
  <li>Be a person not currently serving a sentence, probation, or parole because of a felony conviction</li>
</ol>

