<h4>Resources for Registering to Vote</h4>
<ul>
  <li><h6>How to Register By Mail</h6></li>
  You can register by mail-in form for any state in the US: <a href="https://www.eac.gov/voters/national-mail-voter-registration-form/"> National Mail Registration Form.</a>
  To register, simply download the form from the above page in you prefered language, and fill it out following the state-specific instructions for your state.
  Then, sign and seal the form in an envelope, and send to your state or local election office. Election offices can be found with a simple search,
  such as: "Election office address for 'MY STATE'"
  <li><h6>Polling Place Search</h6></li>
  In order to find your local voting location in New Jersey you can visit this site: <a href="https://www.eac.gov/voters/national-mail-voter-registration-form/">Polling Place Search </a>
  <li><h6>TCNJ Votes!</h6></li>
